1. Once they're launched, their time is frozen, effectively  it. Launch enough people, eventually it will increase the amount of people in existence by stretching out the existence of an ever-increasing set of the population. However, attributing this to time dilation entirely is kinda wonky, I'll agree, so I'm removing the mention of it but keeping the procedure the same.

2. It's a thing that is unfathomably powerful, and as mentioned by the O5,  This is in effect like a disease developing antibiotic resistance. Overuse of antibiotics will utterly screw over the people attempting to stay disease-free. In this case, the disease is the chronovore, and the antibiotic is the calendar.







